<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-697-709 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 697 709</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  April 18 1991 v36 n8A p42(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Valley hiring strongest among smaller concerns. (Region profile:Northern California)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Colborn, Kate.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>There are signs of a thaw in the hiring freeze that has grippedthe Silicon Valley, but the heat is to be found at smallercompanies, especially in the niche semiconductor anddesign-automation arenas.andP;  Integrated circuit vendors, includingCirrus Logic, LSI Logic, and VLSI Technology are aggressivelyseeking engineers with a broad range of skills.andP;  Software firmshave hardly noticed the recession, one source reports.andP;  DesignAutomation, a spinoff of VLSI Technology, will add 50 engineersduring 1991.andP;  Claris Corp, a designer of software for Appleproducts, will also add up to 50 engineers this year, and isparticularly interested in developers with Microsoft Windowsexperience, as it is seeking to increase the portability andcompatibility of its Macintosh applications.andP;  Some firms may bewilling to relocate an exceptional candidate.andP;  Northeast of theSilicon Valley, the Grass Valley Group is looking for more than 30engineers across the range of specialities, including hardware,software, marketing and sales.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Design Automation Consultants (Recruiting)Claris Corp. (Recruiting)Grass Valley Group Inc. (Recruiting).andO;Topic:     Electronic IndustryEmployment OpportunitySilicon ValleyRecruitmentEngineering.andO;Feature:   illustrationtablemap.andO;Caption:   Hiring at a glance. (table)Salary snapshot: focus on the Bay Area. (map)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>